==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petronel
<hw>Pet`ro*nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>petrinal</ets>, fr. <ets>peitrine</ets>, <ets>petrine</ets>, the
breast, F. <ets>poitrine</ets>; so called because it was placed against
the breast in order to fire. See <er>Poitrel</er>.]</ety> <def>A sort of
hand cannon, or portable firearm, used in France in the 15th
century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

